3... c5
{ This variation has started to become fairly popular @@StartBracket@@and then extremely popular!@@EndBracket@@ in the last decade. Since Black is immediately provoking conflict in the center, it is only natural that play here is quickly becoming pretty forcing, unlike after  3...Bf5  , where the strategic understanding and knowledge of plans can often nearly completely eliminate one's need to know the forcing lines.   3...Bf5  is the historical main line. It is still the most popular continuation nowadays, but the difference is that back in the day, only  3...Bf5  was considered reputable, while now  3...c5  gets a fair share of respect as well. }
