6... dxe4
{ Taking is a logical move, and it has been tried in 2 of the 5 games that saw the move 6.a3. Black prevents us from ever taking more space with d4-d5, or from winning the d5-pawn, and reaches the structure typical for the Rubinstein variation.   6...Qd8  7.f4Ν  results in a similar position as the one after @@StartFEN@@rnb1kb1r/ppp2pp1/4pq1p/3p4/3PP3/P1N5/1PP2PPP/R2QKBNR b KQkq - 0 6@@EndFEN@@  6...c6  7.Qd2  . }
