9... Qe7 10. Qf3
{ The queen is headed to g3, from where it can prevent the ...e6-e5 break, while also making room for queenside castling! }
10... O-O
{ Black can also just castle, delaying any pawn break-related decisions. } 11.
O-O-O
{ We also just castle, getting ready for some active play. What kind of active play? Black has no defenders on the kingside, so why don't we go for a kingside attack? }
11... Nd7
{ This knight move enables Black to start preparing ...c7-c5 or ...e6-e5, but it also doesn't bother us and gives us the time to launch a powerful attack. }
12. Rg1
{ Moves like g2-g4 right away, or h2-h4, are also decent. But I really like the idea of getting the rook involved! The attack is very dangerous for Black because the pawn on h6 creates a 'hook' − a way for us to open the files very rapidly. }
12... e5 { Black can try to open up the center, but it's too late. } 13. g4
{ We just ignore it. } 13... exd4 14. g5
{ The files need to get opened no matter what! } 14... hxg5 15. Rxg5
{ With moves like Bc4, Rdg1, Qg3, or Qh5 coming next, Black is absolutely doomed and will get mated in no time! }
*

