{ Black can avoid losing a piece due to this typical clever defense, but the position is still completely lost. }
12. exf6 hxg5 13. fxg7
{ Not only do we win a pawn, but our extra pawn on g7 is extremely powerful! }
13... Rg8 14. h4
{ And with this key move, we show the opponent that the game is about to end. Once the h-file opens up on the next turn, it becomes obvious Black cannot prevent our rook from invading on h8, which means the game will be over. }
