O-O { White is happy to offer a pawn sacrifice! Or, at least, so it seems. }
10... Bxd3 11. Qxd3
{ Next, we can consider playing for the f2-f4-f5 plan with Nh2 and then f2-f4, or try to use our space with Ne4, Nc5, and so on. But, I like the idea of capturing on d5, forcing ...cxd5, and then, in that symmetrical structure, slowly but surely building up the kingside pressure with Nh2, Qg3, Ng4, f2-f4, and so on. White is clearly calling the shots in this fairly standard position! }
