11... Ndb4 { Not a bad move. } 12. Bg5
{ I'd like to force a trade of the dark-squared bishops. To be honest, that's a bit of a pipe dream, because doing so would achieve two overwhelmingly important things:  The c5-pawn will no longer be under attack and could be potentially retained. The check on d6 with the knight would become a magnitude more powerful since Black won't be able to eliminate our knight. So, Black needs to enter a somewhat forced sequence.     12.O-O  isn't something I am interested in, because this move drives the king further away from the center − that's not a good thing in the endgame! − while also allowing Black to effortlessly develop:  12...Bxc5  , with initiative. }
12... Nc2+ 13. Ke2 Nxa1 14. Bxd8 Kxd8 { The forced sequence keeps going on. }
