{ Black must protect the d5-pawn. } 7. Nc3 Nxe5
{ As usual, taking this pawn is too dangerous. } 8. cxd5 exd5 9. Bb5+
{ We manage to develop extremely fast. Soon, the open e-file will become a huge problem for Black, as the pinned knight on e5 can easily find itself a victim of a pin after Re1 or Qe2. }
9... Bd7
{ This leads to an immediate disaster. Also, after  9...Nd7  10.Nxd5+-  , it seems that Black cannot  stop Bf4 and Nc7+, which means huge material gains are right around the corner. }
10. Qe2 { f2-f4 is coming, threatening to win the knight. } 10... Qe7
{ Black's only hope is to solve the pin, but now we win on the spot. } 11. Nxd5
Qd6 12. Bxd7+
{ Black is forced to capture with the king, as the queen is stuck protecting the knight. }
12... Kxd7 13. Qb5+ { The poor king isn't getting even a moment of rest. }
13... Kd8 14. O-O
{ With Rd1 coming next, and the king stuck on d8, there is no doubt White's attack is about to reach its goal within a few short moves. }
