{ Seeking a queen trade is not illogical but doesn't exactly help Black reach full equality. }
17. Qxb4 Bxb4 18. a3
{ The bishop cannot go to e7, as we'd win it; the d6-square isn't available either due to Bxf6 followed by Rxd6. It doesn't make sense to go to a5 due to b2-b4 and b4-b5 winning a ton of time and space. So, Black seems forced to trade on c3. }
