4. dxc5
{ This is considered to be the reason why the otherwise practical and cunning 3...Nf6 isn't more popular. Now, Black is forced to enter a somewhat forced and somewhat unpleasant variation. }
4... Nxe4 5. cxd6 { Now, Black has to know a precise continuation. } 5... e6
{ This is not good since the c8-bishop would now remain passive. We will just develop in the most natural way. }
6. Bd3 Nxd6 7. Nc3 Be7 8. Qe2
{ We could have also chosen to castle kingside first. However, it seems a lot more ambitious, principled, and justified to play Bf4, castle queenside, and create a ton of issues for Black both on the d-file and on the kingside. This should work great, since all of our pieces are aimed there, and Black's knight isn't on f6 anymore, which means the kingside lacks defenders. }
