12... dxe5 13. Qxe5
{ If we are given a few moves, we'd play Rg1, Ne4, and likely get a decisive attack on the kingside. So, Black must rush and trade queens. }
13... Qb8
{ Exactly this move! If we retreat, Black is hoping to make use of the f4-square somehow. For example, with ...Nd5 and ...Nf4 or ...Qf4. }
14. f4
{ we get an interesting middlegame. Black doesn't want to trade, of course, as that would fix White's pawn structure, and kick the black knight out − where would it even go? Next, we'll proceed with Rg1, Qe3, and maybe Ne4, and will keep bothering the black king.   I prefer White here, mostly because our king seems much safer. However, the engine seems to think the position is balanced. That is probably correct, objectively, but in practice, I'd imagine it would be much harder to play with Black, which is why most players don't play the @@StartFEN@@r2q1rk1/pp2bppp/2bppn2/4P1B1/3Q4/2N2N2/PPP2PPP/2KRR3 b - - 0 11@@EndFEN@@  11...Bxf3  variation. :@@EndBracket@@ }
