{ We are trying to trap the opponent's knight! If we had one more tempo, Bh4! would win that piece. }
20... e4 { Black must rush the e-pawn down the board to save the knight. } 21.
Bg5
{ We prevent ...e4-e3 and are getting ready to play Be3 and win the knight. }
21... e3 22. Bxe3
{ We have the same endgame as earlier, where we are much better because of the superior minor piece. }
22... Rae8 23. Bxf2 Rxe1+ 24. Bxe1 Rxe1+ 25. Kd2
{ We have a double attack: there is a threat of checkmate in one move, and the a7-pawn is hanging. }
25... Re8 26. Rxa7 { The endgame is completely winning, of course. } *

