{ Next, we plan on capturing on f6, and then harassing Black's kingside with moves like Ne4 and Qf3, which create threats, while also winning time. }
12... Qd8 13. Bxf6 gxf6
{ I am sure that we could make a lot of good moves, such as Qg4, preparing Rad1, and maybe some sacrifices. But instead, it makes sense to immediately look for the most forcing solutions, as Black is tremendously lacking development. }
14. Nxe6
{ We can afford this move! Let me show you a few fun lines.  14.Qf3  is also game over since the knight on d4 is taboo and Rad1 is coming next.  14...Qxd4  15.Rad1  Qh4  16.Nd5  and Black is busted. }
14... Bxe6
{ 14...Qxd1  15.Ng7+  Kd7  16.Raxd1+  Kc6  17.Ne8  results in a completely winning endgame for White, who has the extra pawn, the better structure, and a very strong attack.   14...fxe6??  15.Qh5+  Ke7  16.Rad1  and with Nd5+ coming next, the black king is getting dragged out in the center, on the d-file, and any discovered check will finish things off. The game is over, ladies and gentlemen! }
15. Qh5
{ Black is temporarily a piece up but is suffering because of the pins. Now, we are threatening to capture on e6 with our rook, taking advantage of the pinned f7-pawn. }
15... Qd7 16. Nd5
{ Now, we have several more threats, such as:  Nxf6, forking the queen and the king; Nb6, forking the queen and the rook; the least obvious one, but the most important one, is Rxe6+ Qxe6 Nc7+, forking the king and the queen from another side.    The game is coming to an end, as Black cannot avoid instant decisive material losses. However, if you don't feel comfortable winning this fast, just play @@StartFEN@@r1bqkb1r/1p3p1p/p3pp2/8/3N4/2N5/PPP2PPP/R2QR1K1 w kq - 0 14@@EndFEN@@  14.Qg4  or something instead of sacrificing the knight. :@@EndBracket@@   Hopefully, such variations will give you a good taste of what a strong lead in development looks like, and why variations like @@StartFEN@@r1bqkbnr/pp1ppppp/2n5/2p5/4P3/5N2/PPPP1PPP/RNBQKB1R w KQkq - 2 3@@EndFEN@@  3.Bb5  Qc7  , which actually might not look that bad at a first glance, are so unpopular with the stronger players. }
