14. Nxd4 Nc6 15. Be3 Nxd4
{ Black gets to trade down, but this position is still clearly inferior. } 16.
Bxd4 d6 17. Bb3
{ I have no doubt that the engine would easily defend the position with only one real weakness  (the d6-pawn)  , but from a human perspective, White seems clearly better. We want Black to trade on d4, helping us activate the queen. Then, we'll play moves like Rfd1, threatening to win the d6-pawn and making the opponent become very passive, Bd5, Rac1, and so on. }
