6... Qb6
{ Black is attacking the knight on d4, making us release the tension in the center. }
7. Nxc6
{ We take exactly with the knight, in order to either keep the bishop pair, or win a lot of time if Black takes our bishop. }
7... Qxb5 { This is a waste of time. } 8. Nd4 Qb6 9. Nc3
{ Black's development is rather awkward since the knight is blocking the kingside pieces. }
9... Nc6 10. Ndb5
{ Black can hardly prevent our knight from invading on d6, which is obviously a very bad outcome. White is much better. }
