{ This is the other major choice. White keeps the tension, continuing to make useful developing moves. }
4... Nge7
{ With this move, Black is preventing the doubled pawns for good. Next, would love to play ...a7-a6, kicking the bishop away. Here, most people try  5.Re1  and  5.c3  , but I would rather suggest a more forcing path. }
