9... Qb6
{ Black is attacking the b5-bishop, pretty much forcing White to take. } 10.
Bxc6
{ Now, Black has a choice. The pawn recapture has been the main move by far, but Daniil Dubov, the main proponent of this line from the Black side, has also tried the queen recapture against Anand! }
10... Qxc6
{ Now, I believe, Anand reacted very reasonably and got a great position. } 11.
dxc5 Nxc5 12. Na3
{ White's main advantage is the limited scope of the g7-bishop and a fantastic outpost on d4. That's exactly where we're bringing the knight: the next moves will be Nc2-d4. }
