Qe2
{ This rare move, which has never been seen at the top level, is an interesting alternative to the main line! It's been tried by two 2500-2600-rated White players in the last two years. }
10... cxd4 11. cxd4 Bd7
{ Black is creating threats like ...Nxe5, as the b5-bishop is loose. } 12. Ba4
{ White stops any potential problems related to the hanging b5-bishop and to the potential tactics with ...Nxe5 or ...Nxd4. Now the tactics don't work, while if Black just develops, White will try to consolidate with Nc3, h2-h3. If we manage to do that, we will get a clear advantage thanks to the extra space, as well as the fact that the g7-bishop is pretty useless. I think we can stop the trainable line here, but it's worth pointing out one more thing. }
12... Nxe5 13. dxe5
{ This doesn't work out for Black. The e3-bishop comes in very handy, as the queen on b6 queen is hanging. Black just lost a piece. }
