11... Nxc3
{ This has been Black's main reaction, and for a good reason. Black is concerned about the weak c6-pawn and closes the c-file so that White cannot attack the c6-pawn with major pieces in the future. }
12. bxc3 Qa5
{ This active move is Black's only chance to at least somehow bother us. } 13.
a4
{ This super-rare move, which was featured in only two games so far, is also very promising. White is preparing Ba3 and does not even mind sacrificing a pawn on c3. However, I am not recommending it as the main line, or as the only line, as many of you would not want to sacrifice for no immediate benefits or gains. }
13... Bg4
{ Black had to push their luck by taking on c3!  13...Qxc3  14.Ba3  and  now, Black needs to waste time defending the e7-pawn.  14...Re8  15.a5!  White has some very promising compensation. Once we install the  bishop on c5, the black queen would be in danger. Instead, if Black takes on a5, we capture on e7, taking advantage of a discovered attack on the queen. Then, we can either play for the queenside initiative or try to attack on the kingside with ideas like Qd2-f4/g5, Bf6, h4-h5-h6, etc. }
14. Ba3
{ White's move in the game is not logical, as the only point of a4 was to develop the bishop here. Now Black is in a lot of strategic trouble.   14.Bg5?!  is inconsistent, and White lost soon.  14...Qxc3  0-1 Rossi-Steinfl, Italy 1995. }
14... Rfe8 15. h3 { We are taking away the opponent's bishop pair. } 15... Bxf3
16. Qxf3 e6 17. Bd6 { White is taking the b8-square under control. } 17... Bf8
{ Black tries to challenge the powerful bishop, but by doing so, weakens the kingside. }
18. Reb1
{ Now we are preparing Rb7, looking to invade on the 7th rank with a decisive attack on the opponent's king. }
18... Bxd6 { Black must get rid of our bishop in order to prepare ...Rab8. }
19. exd6 Rab8 20. h4
{ Black managed to challenge us over the b-file, but now we got a strong d6-pawn and a lot of initiative on the kingside thanks to h4-h5-h6 ideas combined with Qf6. If Black stops us with ...h7-h5, Black needs to be ready for g2-g4!, which can destroy the king's shelter extremely fast. }
